2026-06-16  Tweak: darkened the vertical-ellipsis drag handles in light mode (rail reorder, task-row drag, members-panel assign) — were too faint (zinc-300/zinc-500); now zinc-600. Dark mode unchanged.
2026-06-16  Arc 5 (Wide-Width Layout) complete: all items + O&C (1-12 incl. 12.9-12.11) shipped and the in-browser testing pass (item 13) is green. Marked complete in the milestone arc table.
2026-06-16  Arc 6 item 10.3 (direction change): account-deletion handoff transfers ownership to the highest-ranked surviving member (editor > viewer+ > viewer; oldest joiner breaks ties) instead of routing to Trash — keeps owner_id non-null, no schema change.
2026-06-16  Arc 6 +items 11-14 (draft): undo re-scoped to one shared per-Initiative timeline (supersedes the per-user stack from items 2-3/6) + viewer+ cutoff + depth 500; text edits coalesce per focus→blur; undo/redo selects + scrolls the affected task.
2026-06-16  Arc 6 item 10.3 implemented: account deletion transfers each owned multi-member Initiative to its successor (Initiatives.successor_member/1 — editor > viewer+ > viewer, oldest joiner) instead of blocking; delete_account hands off then deletes, and the account page drops the old block path/copy. Tests cover the selection rule.
2026-06-16  Arc 6 item 11 implemented: undo/redo now run on one shared per-Initiative timeline (replacing the per-user stack from items 2-3/6) — anyone with rights reverses the newest action. Candidates take a %User{} and gate by role: owner/editor undo any task op, a viewer+ only progress on a led task or staffing a descendant (first out-of-rights op walls them), a plain viewer none. Shared redo cleared by any member fresh action; depth 500/Initiative.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 items 12/13: title & description commit on blur (phx-debounce=blur), so a text edit is one undo step per focus→blur (native field-undo stays intact while typing); undo/redo now select + scroll the affected task into view (push "select-task" → TaskKeys hook → DoitSelection.set, skipped when the task vanished, e.g. undo of a create).
2026-06-17  Arc 6 +item 14 O&C (draft): viewer+ grant applies live on assignment; optimistic drag-to-assign; live comments; undo/redo broadcasts per-kind incrementally instead of a full-tree reload for everyone (+ drop the performer redundant load_tree); comment add becomes an undoable event. Testing renumbered to item 15 with the new [Human] checks.
2026-06-17  Backlog: taskmaster (task-scoped full-control role, step up from viewer+); live chat for concurrent viewers (lower-left); editable comments + edit-history and deletable comments with a tombstone (Arc 7).
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14.1: viewer+ grant now applies live — patch_task re-derives led_task_ids (not just the viewer+ label), so being assigned a task by another member grants the subtree affordances with no refresh.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14.2: drag-to-assign is optimistic — dropping a member on an unassigned task fills the primary assignee pill immediately from the member display data carried on the drag element; the server patch reconciles, a rejected/timed-out reply reverts. (Dropping onto an already-assigned task adds a co-assignee, still rendered on the server patch.)
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14.3: scoped the {:comment_added} handler to the commented task — a viewer with that task open refreshes its comments live, while other viewers no longer reload their pane on every comment Initiative-wide. (The comment list already re-rendered on reassign — no phx-update:ignore — so this scopes/lightens an already-live path.)
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14.4: undo/redo broadcast the kind-appropriate message (Tasks.reversal_broadcast) — {:task_updated} for value edits, {:task_moved} for move/reorder, structural {:task_created}/{:task_deleted} for create/delete by direction — instead of a blanket {:task_created}; and the performer patches just the row for value edits rather than a full load_tree. Cost proportional to the change, for everyone.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14.5: comments are undoable — comments gain deleted_at (soft-delete), the "commented" event joins @undoable_kinds, undo soft-deletes the comment and redo restores it (id/body/author preserved), list_comments filters deleted_at, the reversal broadcasts {:comment_added} so viewers refresh, and a viewer+ may undo a comment on their led subtree. Completes item 14 (O&C); Arc 6 now needs only the item-15 [Human] gate.
2026-06-17  Bug fix (item 13 regression): every undo/redo crashed the performer LiveView — the "select-task" push sent task_id as an integer, the client re-emitted it to select_task, and String.to_integer/1 crashed on the integer, re-mounting the page and masking the (already-succeeded) reversal. Push the id as a string; hardened the item-13 test to round-trip select_task so it can not recur.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 +item 14 (draft): make completion (done ⇄ open) undoable — record status_changed + its inverse incl. the Arc-3 cascade-complete (deferred in item 2), closing the "every mutation reversible" goal. Core undo work, not O&C (that is out-of-arc gaps). O&C renumbered to item 15, Testing gate to item 16.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14 (draft) scope expanded after the Cheese "Nothing to undo" repro: completing a leaf records no status event and fragments into per-ancestor progress_changed up to the root (done=>manual_progress coupling + cascade), so an out-of-domain root event walls a viewer+ off from undoing their own in-subtree completion. Item 14 now records one atomic completion event on the acted task (covers the up/down cascade, no fragmentation). The 16.2 testing item notes the surfaced failure (re-verified at 16.9) instead of burying it under the passing cutoff check.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 14 implemented: completion (done <-> open) is undoable. toggle_complete/cascade_status now record ONE atomic status_changed event on the task the user toggled, its inverse_payload capturing every task the flip touched (acted task + cascaded ancestors + cascaded descendants) with prior/next status+manual_progress; the per-task progress_changed spam is suppressed (update_task record_events?: false). undo/redo restore the whole cascade in one step and reconcile roll-ups; rights-gated on the acted task so a viewer+ can undo a completion in their led subtree (fixes the Cheese "Nothing to undo" where an out-of-domain root event walled them off). Reversal broadcasts a structural reload since roll-ups ripple to ancestors. 250 tests green.
